channel.title: Industry on Logos & Brands
channel.description: Recent content in Industry on Logos & Brands

item.title: Education
item.description: Education brands & logo design concepts Get ideas for your educational logo by browsing our gallery of educational institution logos of all sizes and types. Then check out our best practices to see which colors, fonts, and symbols are the best in the industry. Whether a company is a daycare or a college, an international university, or a small school, the right brand will help attract students to the classroom. To increase attendance and bring knowledge to more students, one must create a brand showcasing your expertise, starting with a well-designed educational logo.

item.title: Accounting
item.description: Accounting brands & logo design concepts Before you can create your logo for accounting, you’ll need a bit of inspiration. Luckily for you, we’ve rounded up the logos of some of the biggest accounting companies, as well as helpful logo design tips. Customers should be able to trust more than just your numbers. If your brand can’t be trusted, customers will have difficulty trusting you — no matter how excellent your skills are.

item.title: Agriculture
item.description: Agriculture brands & logo design concepts Before designing an agro logo, check out some of the primary logo trends in the growing sector. Browse our collection of agricultural logos for consulting firms, farms, equipment and supplies, and other agricultural businesses. Whether you were only sowing the seeds of your farming business or put down roots years ago, you’ll need a good logo for your brand. That will promote loyalty by giving shoppers a reason to return season after season.

item.title: Airline
item.description: Airlines brands & logo design concepts Before your brand can take off, you must first understand the basics of airline branding. Browse the logos of domestic and international airlines and air cargo companies to see what symbols the world’s most famous wings wear. To get passengers to trust an airline with their travel plans, they must trust the airline brand with a solid logo. With the suitable airline logo, attracting passengers and expanding your business will be easy.

item.title: Architecture
item.description: Architecture brands & logo design concepts Before drawing a new logo, check out our collection of architectural logos from companies of all sizes and specializations. Learn what colors, symbols, and fonts other architects use to create their brands and how best to use your favorite industry features in your logo. Architecture brands include architects and architects firms, interior and landscape architecture, industrial design, and others. The design of an architectural brand is more than just a decorative facade of a company; it is a way to show the world the style and craftsmanship inherent in your work.

item.title: Art
item.description: Art brands & logo design concepts Whether you teach drawing lessons, run an art gallery, or are artists, a great brand can convince clients of artistic taste. If you’re looking for inspiration for a logo art design, you’ve come to the right place! Visit our gallery of creative art logos to learn how other companies in the industry translate their aesthetic sense into an attractive brand. The symbol of an art logo should reflect the artwork’s style.

item.title: Automotive
item.description: Automotive brands & logo design concepts To create a car logo that will speak to your customers, you first need to understand the basics of car branding. Start by browsing through our automotive logos collection from all industry areas. Learn the colors, formats, fonts, and symbols that others use to promote a new business and guidelines for using them in your logo. A strong brand and sharp logo can give a company a winning advantage in the race to gain customers.

item.title: Bank
item.description: Banking brands & logo design concepts Start exploring and get inspired by browsing through our collection of bank logos from international financial institutions, innovative fintech companies, and local banks worldwide. See what shapes, objects, and symbols other banks use to build customer trust and learn how to use them in a logo. Before people can trust a bank with their finances, they must first believe in the bank’s security, stability, trust, and credibility.

item.title: Book
item.description: Book brands & logo design concepts Learn which forms and symbols are appropriate for the design of book logos by browsing our gallery of logos for libraries, bookstores, and publishers. Learn which forms and marks are suitable for a logo that turns pages. More often than not, readers will judge a book by its cover and do just that. Create a great first impression of your literary enterprise with an outstanding book logo.

item.title: Charity
item.description: Charity brands & logo design concepts Draw inspiration from a design by browsing our collection of charity logos from charities of all sizes and focuses. After browsing our logo gallery, check out the best practices to see which logo colors, fonts, and symbols best convey your mission. Starting a charity requires passion and determination. But to increase efforts and exert more influence, you need to involve others. The suitable charity logo will tell about the charity cause and inspire others to join the movement.

item.title: Clothing
item.description: Banking brands & logo design concepts In the apparel industry, a logo should look just as good (and fit just as well) as the clothes and accessories the brand sells. In other words, it should convey your sense of style and taste at a glance. For a passionate designer-entrepreneur who loves the latest fashion trends and understands style, there is nothing better than creating a clothing line. Whether creating a new design, delivering from a third-party manufacturer, or working with a designer, a stylish logo on clothing will complement the brand and help stand out from the crowd.

item.title: Consulting
item.description: Consulting brands & logo design concepts Consulting is an ever-evolving industry with diverse qualifications and experience requirements. As a consultant, improving productivity and organization requires a unique combination of analytical and social skills. A well-designed logo will demonstrate that the brand has everything to impact the business significantly. If you want to use the symbol in a consulting logo, match it with the company’s consulting services and ensure it complements other design elements.

item.title: Design & Creative
item.description: Creative and design related brands & logo concepts Whether a company sells art prints, designs custom jewelry or handmade soap, designs websites or videos, or any other creative goods and services, a great logo can showcase its creativity at a glance. To stand out in the creative industry, the company needs a logo that captures its audience’s imagination and inspires them to pay attention to the company’s brand. In addition to matching your company’s offering and other logo design elements, your symbol should be markedly different from the symbols used by your competitors.

item.title: Engineering
item.description: Engineering brands & logo design concepts To build a brand that meets the engineering industry’s standards, one must first understand those standards. Explore trends in engineering branding by browsing through our collection of engineering logos for companies of all sizes and specializations. Because so much depends on the correctness of the company’s calculations, an engineering brand can’t afford a single digit or decimal point to be out of place. But for potential customers to trust the calculations, they must first trust the brand.

item.title: Furniture
item.description: Furniture brands & logo design concepts See how furniture companies are making customers feel comfortable through their creations, as well as through their logos. Sufficiently selected furniture can transform a space – turn a house into a dwelling or an empty room into an office. But before people can trust a company to arrange their space, they have to trust the sense of taste. Showcase the craftsmanship and style behind the furniture company’s creations with a well-designed furniture logo.

item.title: Religion
item.description: Religion brands & logo design concepts To help people find their way to a community such as a church, one must first find a way to communicate beliefs and values to the world, precisely what an excellent religious logo with an iconic symbol can do. Before you begin designing, get inspired by browsing our gallery of church logo designs from congregations of all denominations. Use a church’s history and traditions to find symbols that convey its values and beliefs at a glance.
